title: For Sale:  HAC-7, Holloway Arms 7.62 X 51 RARE tactical rifle
postcontent: This is a like new, HAC-7 rifle in 7.62. I bought this rifle new from Bob Holloway in Ft. Worth, TX. Seems like it was in the early 80's. This one is #305 and Bob told me that less than 300 were actually built. They started out by machining the receivers from solid stock then to keep cost down, tried to investment cast them. The IC ones cracked. The entire project was abandoned. I'm not sure of all the reasons they went out of the rifle business, but lack of quality wasn't one of them. The rifle I have has about one box put through it. I have the box as well which has some water staining on one end. It has been some time ago that I bought this. It is a very, very rare rifle! I did considerable research on this and could find very little information about it. If you want to own one of the rarest assault type rifles in existence, this is your chance. It also comes with a scope mount

title: For Sale:  Spectacular Match Grade AR Service Rifle Comp Ready!
postcontent:
This offering is my custom competition service rifle in AR15.   

This rifle began its life as a Rock River Arms A2 LAR-15.    The upper was sent to White Oak Armaments, one of the top gunsmiths for service rifle competitors in the US.    They completely tore it down and reworked it starting around a Pac Nor match grade stainless steel post-ban barrel with 11 degree target crown.    The barrel is 1 in 7 twist with a Wylde Chamber.  It is free floating under the handguard.    They matched the bolt face to the chamber  and installed a .62 front sight blade.   The rear sight was installed and features ¼ MOA adjustments per click.  I currently have a .46 rear sight hooded aperature, but have several other sizes for it.   The lower was worked over with a two stage jewell trigger that is adjustable for pull and overtravel and breaks like glass.  I have installed lead in the buttstock to perfectly balance the rifle.  This is a heavy rifle, but that makes it rock solid in position.  On my current competition load of a BR2 bench rest primer, 25.4 grains of Varget and a Sierra Match King 75.gr bullet, this rifle will shoot 3/8” groups consistently at 100 yards from bench rest.    

It shoots better than I do, that’s for sure.   The best I’ve managed to post with it is Expert, but I don’t get enough time in at the range to make Master or High Master.  Such is life. :P

This rifle is built to spec for NRA and Civilian Marksmanship Program Matches and comes with a Turner All-Weather 1907 competition sling and hard case.  No ammo, no magazines included.  This rifle has had roughly 500 rounds put through it since it was worked over.

title: For Sale:  PTR-91 15 20-Rd Mags and 800 Rds NATO FN 7.62x51 ammo
location: North Fayetteville/Raleigh/Durham, Raleigh / Durham / CH, North Carolina
postcontent:
Offering is a PTR model 91.    This rifle was born when our Fed gov’t decided in Regulation ATF 922R that any new firearm could not have more than 10 imported parts in it.   At the time the Heckler and Koch model 91 chambered in 7.62 NATO was one of the most popular rifles around and for good reason…

They run like tanks and are very accurate!

This is the civilian version of the German G3 design that has been used by their military since the 1950’s.    http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Heckler_%26_Koch_G3

After the ban on imports,  JLD industries bought the engineering and machining from HK to manufacture the model 91 here in the states.   These rifles have had several evolutions since the original offering and are rock solid performers.  here is the current model listing:

http://www.ptr91.com/rifles

Here are the specs for this particular variation:

18” Button-rifled heavy target barrel in 1 in 12 right hand twist
Semi-auto recoil operated
20 rd box magazine fed
Rotary diopter rear sight with bullet drop compensation set for 100,200,300 and 400 yards
The rifle comes with 15 Magazines, a Brugger and Thomet Picatinny rail mount for optics mount (150 bucks on its own), hard case, sight tool and manual

Bolt and trigger group are manufactured by HK, all other parts are JLD

The trigger is pretty darned good for a rifle of this type

Rifle has about 1000 rounds put down the pipe in its lifetime

To feed this rifle I have for sale 4x200 rds of NATO 7.62 ammo manufactured by Fabrique National of Belgium.   Headstamp is 1977 manufacture.  The only Military Surplus ammo more accurate and reliable than this is the Lithuanian variety and you can’t find either of them anywhere.   If anyone offers them for sale, they are snapped up in seconds.   These are berdan primed cases, so they require a berdan decapping die to reload them.

title: For Sale:  Action Arms Israeli Military Industries (IMI) Uzi Pistol Model 9mm NIB pre-ban
postcontent:
If you want one buy it NOW before it is too late!! Imported by Action Arms the Israeli Military Industries (IMI) Uzi was a revolutionary weapon in that it was the first to use a telescoping bolt design, in which the bolt wraps around the breech end of the barrel. This allows the barrel to be moved far back into the receiver and the magazine to be housed in the pistol grip. The Uzi uses an open bolt, blowback-operated design. The open bolt design exposes the breech end of the barrel, and improves cooling during periods of continuous fire. Used by the Secret Service from the 1960s until the 1990s, the Uzi is known as one of the most compact, yet versatile, personal defense weapons of the past forty years. This Uzi is a new in box pre-ban Pistol Model in 9mm. It's been stored and is in excellent condition. The gun pictured may have a different serial number, but is a NIB Uzi. 
The UZI pistol was developed by Israel Military Industries (now IWI Ltd) during early 1980s from the famous Micro-UZI submachine gun. Intended users for the UZI pistol were various security agencies and services which wanted a high-capacity semi-automatic pistol, and civilian shooters (mostly in USA) which also wanted such gun with "cool Uzi style". Despite somewhat rough appearance UZI pistols were reliable and quite accurate. It also must be noted that 'original' UZI pistols should not be confused with full-size weapons based on semi-automatic only full-size Uzi carbines but without the shoulder stock. 
UZI pistol is blowback-operated semi-automatic weapon which fires from closed bolt. It has a stamped steel receiver and the bolt is fully enclosed inside. Bolt is of 'telescoped' design, that is, it is hollow in the front and encloses the rear part of the barrel when in battery. Uzi pistol has a single action trigger and utilizes an internal sliding striker (firing pin). Manual safety of sliding type, and is located above the grip on the left side of the gun. Magazines are of double stack design, interchangeable with other guns of Uzi family (in 9mm caliber). Sights are of open type, with flip-up rear sight, adjustable for windage.
Details:
• Semi-auto carbine
• 4.5" barrel
• Baked enamel black finish over phosphated (parkerized) base
• 25 round mag
• Original sling
• Original molded plastic and cardboard boxes
• Bayonet lug
• Includes case, cover sleeve, all original literature and accessories
Quick release clip
Additional Charges 
Must pay both FFL dealer charges, shipping and insurance cost. Rifles/shotguns will be shipped either pre-paid or COD. Handguns will only be shipped pre-paid.
